{"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"Overview","text":"Overview","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"code":"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywallUI","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ships three view modifiers that wrap RevenueCatUI’s surfaces with platform-aware presentation. Each is bound to ","type":"text"},{"code":"PaywallState","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": presentation flags drive visibility, and the bindings dispatch matching paywall actions back through the store on dismissal. There is no local sheet state.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"For platform behavior details (iOS ","type":"text"},{"code":"fullScreenCover","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" vs macOS sheet sizing, App Store deep link on macOS), see ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/PlatformBehavior","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Before-you-start","text":"Before you start","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This guide assumes:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You have completed "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/HowToImplementService"},{"type":"text","text":". The plugin is registered and "},{"code":"observeCustomerInfo","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" runs on launch."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Your app target depends on the "},{"code":"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywallUI","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" product:"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"codeListing","code":[".product(name: \"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywallUI\", package: \"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\"),"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Step-1-Attach-both-sheets-to-a-root-view","text":"Step 1: Attach both sheets to a root view","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The simplest wiring uses the ","type":"text"},{"code":"revenueCatPaywall(state:send:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" modifier — one call, both sheets, both dismissals:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["import SwiduxRevenueCatPaywallUI","","struct RootView: View {","    @Environment(AppStore.self) private var store","","    var body: some View {","        ContentView()","            .revenueCatPaywall(state: store.paywall) { action in","                store.send(.paywall(action))","            }","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The closure receives a ","type":"text"},{"code":"PaywallAction","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" (","type":"text"},{"code":".dismiss","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"code":".dismissCustomerCenter","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":") and lifts it into your root action. Place the modifier on the topmost view that should host both sheets.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Both paywall modifiers also accept ","type":"text"},{"code":"displayCloseButton:","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" (default ","type":"text"},{"code":"true","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"). The default presentation has no other way out — see ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/PlatformBehavior","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" before turning it off.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Step-2-Trigger-the-paywall-from-a-feature","text":"Step 2: Trigger the paywall from a feature","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Dispatch ","type":"text"},{"code":".request(reason:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" with a short identifier describing why you’re asking. ","type":"text"},{"code":"PaywallState.requestedReason","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" stores the value so the sheet (or analytics) can tailor its copy:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["Button(\"Export PDF\") {","    store.send(.paywall(.request(reason: \"export-pdf\")))","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The plugin sets ","type":"text"},{"code":"PaywallState.isPresented = true","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". The ","type":"text"},{"code":"revenueCatPaywall","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" modifier observes the change and presents ","type":"text"},{"code":"RevenueCatUI.PaywallView","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Step-3-Trigger-the-customer-center","text":"Step 3: Trigger the customer center","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Existing subscribers manage their subscription through the customer center. Surface a button that dispatches ","type":"text"},{"code":".presentCustomerCenter","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":":","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["if store.paywall.isPro {","    Button(\"Manage Subscription\") {","        store.send(.paywall(.presentCustomerCenter))","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"code":"revenueCatCustomerCenter","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" modifier presents ","type":"text"},{"code":"RevenueCatUI.CustomerCenterView","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" on iOS. On macOS it opens the system App Store subscriptions URL and immediately fires ","type":"text"},{"code":"onDismiss","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" (RevenueCatUI does not ship a customer center on macOS — see ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/PlatformBehavior","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":").","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Step-4-Manual-wiring-optional","text":"Step 4: Manual wiring (optional)","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If you need only one sheet, or you want to interleave other modifiers between them, attach the primitive modifiers directly. Each takes a real ","type":"text"},{"code":"Binding<Bool>","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"; build it with a ","type":"text"},{"code":"set:","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" that dispatches the matching dismiss action when SwiftUI clears the flag:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["ContentView()","    .revenueCatPaywall(","        isPresented: Binding(","            get: { store.paywall.isPresented },","            set: { if !$0 { store.send(.paywall(.dismiss)) } }","        )","    )","    .revenueCatCustomerCenter(","        isPresented: Binding(","            get: { store.paywall.isCustomerCenterPresented },","            set: { if !$0 { store.send(.paywall(.dismissCustomerCenter)) } }","        )","    )"],"syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The convenience modifier ","type":"text"},{"code":"revenueCatPaywall(state:send:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is exactly equivalent to this wiring.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Step-5-Restore-from-inside-the-paywall","text":"Step 5: Restore from inside the paywall","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"RevenueCatUI’s ","type":"text"},{"code":"PaywallView","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" provides its own restore button by default. If you need an additional restore affordance elsewhere (a Settings row, for example), dispatch ","type":"text"},{"code":".restorePurchases","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":":","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["Button(\"Restore Purchases\") {","    store.send(.paywall(.restorePurchases))","}",".disabled(store.paywall.isLoading)"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"What-happens-on-dismiss","text":"What happens on dismiss","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"When the user dismisses the paywall, the plugin’s ","type":"text"},{"code":".dismiss","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" action clears ","type":"text"},{"code":"PaywallState.isPresented","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"requestedReason","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", then dispatches ","type":"text"},{"code":".refreshCustomerInfo","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" so the gate is reconciled — the user may have purchased while the sheet was open.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"When the user dismisses the customer center, the plugin’s ","type":"text"},{"code":".dismissCustomerCenter","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" action clears ","type":"text"},{"code":"isCustomerCenterPresented","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". No refresh is dispatched, since opening the customer center does not change entitlement state by itself; the live ","type":"text"},{"code":"customerInfoStream","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" from ","type":"text"},{"code":"Step 5","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" of ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/HowToImplementService","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" picks up any subscription change RevenueCat reports asynchronously.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/swiduxrevenuecatpaywall\/howtopresenttheui"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/HowToPresentTheUI"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall"]]},"sections":[],"kind":"article","seeAlsoSections":[{"anchor":"Related-Documentation","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/PlatformBehavior","doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/HowToImplementService"],"title":"Related Documentation","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The matching API reference for the views described here lives in the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywallUI"},{"type":"text","text":" documentation."}]},{"anchor":"H